Thorax.
Legs (
Figs 22–23
): epiphysis and arolium present. Venation (
Fig. 25
): fore- and hindwing without Sc1; hindwing CuP absent, 1A and 2A complete; hindwing Sc and Rs separated. Dorsal forewing ornamentation slightly marked by transverse blackish patch between cubital veins which sometimes extends disto-anteriorly, in parallel to outer margin. Ventral forewing, dorsal and ventral hindwing uniformly coloured, sometimes darker distally, unornamented.

Thorax.
Legs (
